study_title: Culina et al., Islet-reactive CD8+ T cell frequencies in the pancreas, but not in blood, distinguish type 1 diabetic patients from healthy donors
inclusion_exclusion_criteria: subjects were included if they had one DRB1*0401 allele and had a diagnosis of T1D, autoantibody positive but no T1D (at-risk), or were healthy controls
lab_address: Benaroya Research Institute, 1201 Ninth Ave, Seattle, WA, 98101, USA
biomaterial_provider: Benaroya Research Institute, 1201 Ninth Ave, Seattle, WA, 98101, USA
tissue_processing: naïve and memory CD4 and CD8 cell populations were sorted by flow cytometry, and DNA was extracted using the Qiagen AllPrep® DNA/RNA/Protein Mini Kit per the manufacturer's instructions.
cell_subset: central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell
cell_isolation: Cells were stained with fluorochrome labeled antibodies and then sorted on a BD FACSAria cytometer
library_generation_protocol: TCR-β chains were sequenced using the immunoSEQ Assay (Adaptive Biotechnologies) as previously described
